1
00:00:00,350 --> 00:00:05,440
Some work because they have to, others are ambitious and work for advancement.

2
00:00:05,790 --> 00:00:16,240
Some associates belittle everything the boss says or does, others are much more objective and realize they must be good followers before they can be good leaders.

3
00:00:17,150 --> 00:00:20,880
how we think is directly affected by the group we're in.

4
00:00:21,070 --> 00:00:24,079
Be sure you're in the flock that thinks right.

5
00:00:24,670 --> 00:00:27,760
There are pitfalls to watch in your work environment.

6
00:00:27,870 --> 00:00:33,040
In every group, there are persons who, secretly aware of their own inadequacies,

7
00:00:33,150 --> 00:00:36,959
want to stand in your way and prevent you from making progress.

8
00:00:37,390 --> 00:00:44,479
Many ambitious fellows have been laughed at, even threatened, because they tried to be more efficient and produce more.

9
00:00:44,590 --> 00:00:51,839
Let's face it, some folks, being jealous, want to make you feel embarrassed because you want to move upward.

10
00:00:52,670 --> 00:00:59,599
This often happens in factories, where fellow workers sometimes resent the fellow who wants to speed up production.

11
00:00:59,869 --> 00:01:10,320
It happens in the military service, when a clique of negative-minded individuals poke fun at and try to humiliate the young soldier who wants to go to officer school.

12
00:01:10,829 --> 00:01:18,399
It happens in business, too, when a few individuals not qualified to advance try to block the way for someone else.

13
00:01:19,230 --> 00:01:31,440
You've seen it happen time and again in high schools when a group of lunkheads deride a classmate who has the good sense to make the most of his educational opportunities and come out with high grades.

14
00:01:31,869 --> 00:01:41,280
Sometimes, and all too sadly often, the bright student is jeered at until he reaches the conclusion that it isn't smart to be intelligent.

15
00:01:41,710 --> 00:01:44,960
Ignore such negative thinkers in your midst.

16
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:51,359
For often, the remarks made in your direction aren't so personal as you might at first think.

17
00:01:51,630 --> 00:01:57,119
They are merely a projection of the speaker's own feeling of failure and discouragement.

18
00:01:57,630 --> 00:02:00,960
Don't let negative thinkers pull you down to their level.

19
00:02:00,990 --> 00:02:05,599
Let them slide by, like the water from the proverbial duck's back.

20
00:02:05,870 --> 00:02:08,480
Cling to people who think progressively.

21
00:02:08,589 --> 00:02:10,320
Move upward with them.

22
00:02:10,510 --> 00:02:13,599
You can do it, simply by thinking right.

23
00:02:14,510 --> 00:02:15,599
A special word of caution.
